n by uncertainty caused by climate change, population growth, food security, energy availability, and other local and global factors. This uncertainty means that there is an ever-growing responsibility to ensure that the actions of today do not compromise the needs of future generations. This second edition of Farmland Preservation provides a range of views and case studies from across Canada, the United States, and beyond. Its fourteen essays are intended to help the reader understand the importance of the issue and the potential for applying new approaches to agricultural protection, policy tools, and initiatives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLand use, Rural. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh  aFarmland, Preservation, Farmland Preservation, Development, Agriculture, Planning, Food Security, Land Use.1 aBrunet, Nicolas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBryant, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBudge, Trevor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButt, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaldwell, Wayne J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCaldwell, Wayne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChahine, Ghalia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChurchyard, Arthur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaniels, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavidson, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDodds, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGranjon, Denis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb